h3. Summary
* If a calendar is not restricted, all users have the ability to delete this calendar.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Have a user A who is only a member of the _site-admins_ and a user B who is only a member of the _confluence-users_ group;
# Have user A to create a calendar in Confluence;
# Have user B to add the existing calendar created by user A;
# Have user B to click on the *...* on the side of the calendar's name and select the option *Remove*;
# User B selects the option "Permanently delete this calendar for all users.";
# User B clicks on *Delete Calendar*;

h3. Expected Results
* Deleting other user's calendar is not possible unless you're a site administrator.

h3. Actual Results
* All users, regardless of being the calendar's creator or a site administrator, can delete a calendar in Confluence.

h3.Workaround
* Enable the edit restrictions of the calendar to allow only specific users to edit it. This way, users who are restricted from editing the calendar won't be able to delete it.

h3. Summary
* If a label is added to a page and this page is edited afterward, this same page won't appear in the Activity Stream macro anymore.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Add the Activity Stream macro in a page;
# Create another page;
# Add a label to this second page;
# Edit the second page and publish it;

h3. Expected Results
* Page shows its updates on the Activity Stream macro.

h3. Actual Results
* Page no longer appears in the Activity Stream macro.

h3.Workaround
N/A
